summary: This is a U.S. Attorney's Office foreign travel questionnaire for an Assistant U.S. Attorney (AUSA) from the Southern District of New York (SDNY) traveling to Stockholm, Sweden from February 3-6, 2020. The purpose is to interview and debrief a witness (Jane Doe) in the ongoing, sensitive investigation into Jeffrey Epstein, with Ghislaine Maxwell identified as a subject.

events.title: Planned Travel to Sweden for Witness Interview
events.description: An AUSA from SDNY, along with an FBI SA and an NYPD detective, plan to travel from New York to Stockholm, Sweden to interview and debrief a witness (Jane Doe) in the Jeffrey Epstein investigation.

keyFacts: In February 2020, U.S. prosecutors from the SDNY were actively investigating Jeffrey Epstein and Ghislaine Maxwell, planning to travel to Sweden to interview a witness.
The investigation was designated as "ongoing and very sensitive" under case number USAO # 2018R01618.
Ghislaine Maxwell is identified as a subject of the investigation and is believed to hold triple citizenship (U.S., U.K., France).
The travel party included an Assistant U.S. Attorney, an FBI Special Agent (Amanda Youn), and an NYPD detective, indicating a multi-agency effort.
Foreign authorities in Sweden had cleared the visit and were prepared to cooperate with the U.S. investigation.
